
Overview of noun mercury

The noun mercury has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                        
1. (6) mercury, quicksilver, hydrargyrum, Hg, atomic number 80 -- (a heavy silvery toxic univalent and bivalent metallic element; the only metal that is liquid at ordinary temperatures)
2. Mercury -- ((Roman mythology) messenger of Jupiter and god of commerce; counterpart of Greek Hermes)
3. Mercury -- (the smallest planet and the nearest to the sun)
4. mercury -- (temperature measured by a mercury thermometer; "the mercury was falling rapidly")
